			<text><![CDATA[Fouling poses many threats to boats. It increases drag on the hull, which reduces speed and leads to increased fuel consumption. Fouling also weighs on the vessel, making it sit lower than usual. In the long-term it can cause significant damage to the boat structure and can ultimately cause leakage and the collapse of the hull. A heavily fouled vessel may also lose manoeuvrability. Finally, fouling reduces the responsiveness of the vessel. A ship with a weakened hull risks capsizing in storm conditions where rapid changes of direction are extremely important. ]]></text>
